members.name: FocusEvent()
members.description: Creates a FocusEvent event with the given parameters.

parameters.name: typeArg
parameters.description: Is a DOMString representing the name of the event.

parameters.name: focusEventInitOptional
parameters.description: Is a FocusEventInit dictionary, having the following fields: "relatedTarget", optional and defaulting to null, is an EventTarget representing the secondary target of a FocusEvent. The FocusEventInit dictionary also accepts fields from the UIEventInit and EventInit dictionaries.

members.name: FocusEvent.relatedTarget
members.description: Is an EventTarget representing a secondary target for this event. As in some cases (like when tabbing in or out a page), this property may be set to null for security reasons.
